(Young Duan Zhixing)

2
00:00:13,199 --> 00:00:14,599
His Majesty asked me to teach you

3
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:16,960
not merely about the art of chess,

4
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,039
but the ways of a sovereign.

5
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:20,960
I remember it.

6
00:00:21,239 --> 00:00:23,480
You shouldn't limit yourself

7
00:00:23,559 --> 00:00:25,519
to analyzing short-term gains or losses.

8
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:26,640
Teacher.

9
00:00:26,839 --> 00:00:27,879
My father has left.

10
00:00:31,839 --> 00:00:34,000
Practice swordsmanship now!

11
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:37,159
Teacher.

12
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:38,920
Is the martial world as captivating

13
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:40,119
as described in the books?

14
00:00:40,359 --> 00:00:41,840
(Legend of Hero Xiao Feng Vol.3)
Master Xu Zhu

15
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,880
merely solved

16
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:46,439
Wuyazi's Mystical Chess Puzzle,

17
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:49,880
and gained peerless martial arts.

18
00:00:52,159 --> 00:00:54,200
I wish I could wander

19
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:55,000
the martial world.

20
00:00:55,359 --> 00:00:57,000
It's boring here.

21
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:06,079
Hey, eating your cake?

22
00:01:08,719 --> 00:01:09,359
Beat him!

23
00:01:11,359 --> 00:01:11,959
What's wrong?

24
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:13,680
Come here.

25
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:16,319
How can you beat your master?

26
00:01:16,879 --> 00:01:18,239
Brat! I'll kill you!

27
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:21,079
Move!

28
00:01:33,632 --> 00:01:35,424
(The Legend of Heroes)

29
00:02:54,304 --> 00:02:55,234
=Duel on Mount Hua=

30
00:02:55,234 --> 00:02:57,509
(Adapted from Jin Yong's novel,
The Legend of the Condor Heroes)

31
00:02:57,509 --> 00:03:00,448
=Southern Emperor and Northern Beggar=
=Episode 2=

32
00:03:18,759 --> 00:03:19,719
Weird.

33
00:03:30,319 --> 00:03:31,560
Where is this place?

34
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,360
Where is this place?

35
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:53,439
Why am I on a ship?

36
00:03:53,879 --> 00:03:54,800
Who are you?

37
00:03:55,159 --> 00:03:56,319
Why are you capturing me?

38
00:04:06,159 --> 00:04:07,000
Let go of me!

39
00:04:07,639 --> 00:04:08,800
Who are you?

40
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:10,520
What did you feed me?

41
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,719
Why can't I muster

42
00:04:11,759 --> 00:04:12,560
any strength?

43
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:17,079
This drug is called Driftwood Powder.

44
00:04:17,759 --> 00:04:18,639
(Nuowu Tribe's Young Master of Wuman, Yi Huo)
After taking it,

45
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,639
you're like wood drifting on water,

46
00:04:21,319 --> 00:04:22,560
incapable

47
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:23,959
of resistance.

48
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:25,800
I hold no grudges

49
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:26,839
against you people.

50
00:04:27,279 --> 00:04:28,040
Why waste

51
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,040
such precious drug

52
00:04:29,079 --> 00:04:30,160
on me?

53
00:04:30,519 --> 00:04:31,199
Don't worry.

54
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:32,959
You'll die soon.

55
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,839
The cheap lives longest.

56
00:04:35,519 --> 00:04:37,480
I only worth seven coins,

57
00:04:37,839 --> 00:04:38,959
so I can live long...

58
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,800
You've captured the wrong person!

59
00:04:42,519 --> 00:04:44,040
Royal guards have pursued you.

60
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:45,040
Could they go wrong?

61
00:04:45,639 --> 00:04:46,319
I don't know

62
00:04:46,319 --> 00:04:47,959
why they pursued me.

63
00:04:54,519 --> 00:04:55,240
I-I...

64
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,360
Any last words?

65
00:04:57,639 --> 00:04:59,160
Someone gave me this.

66
00:04:59,160 --> 00:04:59,680
Who?

67
00:05:00,399 --> 00:05:00,920
Well...

68
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,240
I forgot to ask his name.

69
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,560
Indeed, sounds absurd.

70
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,279
What for?

71
00:05:09,759 --> 00:05:10,720
A trade of sorts.

72
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:11,399
For what?

73
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:12,680
A ragged sack.

74
00:05:14,759 --> 00:05:16,079
That sounds ridiculous!

75
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,000
Fooling me again?

76
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,120
What do you mean by

77
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,079
"again"?

78
00:05:24,128 --> 00:05:26,600
(Dali, Imperial Palace)

79
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,639
The conflict between Wuman

80
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:30,439
and Dali has caused

81
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,040
countless casualties.

82
00:05:32,519 --> 00:05:33,079
Recently,

83
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:34,879
I have realized

84
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,480
that Dali can

85
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,680
embrace all peoples.

86
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:40,240
Therefore,

87
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:42,600
I sent envoys to tribes to proclaim

88
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,920
our desire for lasting peace

89
00:05:46,759 --> 00:05:48,720
to end all warfare.

90
00:05:49,319 --> 00:05:49,839
What

91
00:05:50,519 --> 00:05:51,720
do you think?

92
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:52,672
Your Majesty.

93
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,360
We Wuman

94
00:05:54,759 --> 00:05:56,160
are rugged folk,

95
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,079
but we aren't warmongers.

96
00:05:59,079 --> 00:06:00,439
We gladly end the war

97
00:06:00,839 --> 00:06:02,199
to farm and hunt peacefully.

98
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,399
And

99
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,720
(Wuman Envoy, Leader)
we nominate

100
00:06:05,199 --> 00:06:07,120
Yi Huo, daughter
of Nuowu Tribe's leader,

101
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,439
to marry the prince.

102
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:10,319
May they bear

103
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:11,759
numerous heirs.

104
00:06:14,439 --> 00:06:14,839
Here.

105
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:24,759
The Feng Blade

106
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,439
accompany the Crown Prince
since his birth.

107
00:06:26,959 --> 00:06:27,759
And I'll give

108
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:28,480
this

109
00:06:28,879 --> 00:06:30,040
Huang Blade to Miss Yi Huo

110
00:06:30,639 --> 00:06:31,519
as the betrothal gift.

111
00:06:33,879 --> 00:06:35,000
You broke the engagement

112
00:06:35,279 --> 00:06:36,560
and humiliated me once.

113
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,600
It's a serious matter.

114
00:06:42,399 --> 00:06:44,480
This whip strike
is for your selfishness.

115
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:47,240
This, for your refusal to admit fault.

116
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,199
And this,

117
00:06:53,319 --> 00:06:54,360
for your loud voice!

118
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,199
I'm innocent, yet no one

119
00:06:58,199 --> 00:06:59,000
can prove it.

120
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,720
I'm the truly innocent

121
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:01,560
one.

122
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:02,920
You?

123
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,279
After you escaped,

124
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,720
rumors spread throughout Dali,

125
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:08,040
claiming our young master is hideous

126
00:07:08,399 --> 00:07:09,720
and you'd rather escape

127
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,360
than marry!

128
00:07:11,399 --> 00:07:12,680
This is simple!

129
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:15,079
You're beautiful.

130
00:07:15,399 --> 00:07:16,240
Just let me go

131
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,199
and I'll go

132
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,360
clear your name.

133
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,639
Easy for you to say.

134
00:07:20,439 --> 00:07:21,360
All tribes of Dali

135
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,000
are mocking Nuowu Tribe.

136
00:07:23,839 --> 00:07:25,639
Our young master lost all dignity.

137
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,600
By Nuowu custom,

138
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,439
I shall punish you!

139
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:32,079
Men who tarnish women's reputations

140
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,680
don't deserve manhood.

141
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:36,839
Drown him.

142
00:07:37,439 --> 00:07:38,040
No way!

143
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,720
No! Absolutely not!

144
00:07:40,759 --> 00:07:41,680
Well...

145
00:07:42,079 --> 00:07:42,639
No way!

146
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:43,199
No way!

147
00:07:43,879 --> 00:07:45,360
Let me explain!

148
00:07:50,199 --> 00:07:50,439
Stop.

149
00:07:54,319 --> 00:07:54,480
Go.

150
00:07:58,399 --> 00:07:58,656
You!

151
00:08:01,079 --> 00:08:01,376
Go.

152
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:14,399
Bro.

153
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,240
Lucky.

154
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:15,959
Lucky.

155
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,199
Why are you here?

156
00:08:17,399 --> 00:08:18,439
I'm queuing to exit.

157
00:08:18,519 --> 00:08:18,879
You?

158
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:19,800
Begging for food.

159
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,000
Want some?

160
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:22,360
I'm queuing.

161
00:08:23,079 --> 00:08:23,720
To exit,

162
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:24,680
you need a permit.

163
00:08:25,319 --> 00:08:26,120
(Permit)
Where's your permit?

164
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,199
Right, I need a permit.

165
00:08:30,759 --> 00:08:31,639
Just go.

166
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:32,519
We are waiting.

167
00:08:32,519 --> 00:08:33,080
Hurry!

168
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:33,240
Go.

169
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,480
We're all waiting!

170
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,279
Fine. You go first.

171
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:38,000
Go!

172
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,128
Where's your permit?

173
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:45,759
I lost it.

174
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:46,960
Lost it?

175
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,360
As beggars,

176
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:50,840
losing things is our specialty.

177
00:08:51,679 --> 00:08:52,919
We have exclusive passages.

178
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:55,279
Come with me.

179
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:56,720
Come.

180
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,080
Next.

181
00:08:59,559 --> 00:09:01,159
Drowning me won't help.

182
00:09:01,399 --> 00:09:02,600
In my humble opinion,

183
00:09:02,799 --> 00:09:03,960
this act can't restore

184
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:04,879
your reputation.

185
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,879
I have a plan.

186
00:09:14,039 --> 00:09:14,679
What is it?

187
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,720
Kill me now,

188
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,720
and gossips will claim

189
00:09:18,879 --> 00:09:20,480
you acted from shame.

190
00:09:20,879 --> 00:09:22,320
That'd confirm the rumors

191
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,600
that you are hideous.

192
00:09:23,879 --> 00:09:24,639
What did you say?

193
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:25,559
Drown him!

194
00:09:25,919 --> 00:09:26,840
Wait, I...

195
00:09:27,039 --> 00:09:27,919
Wait, I'm sorry.

196
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,080
Wait!

197
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:30,799
Listen.

198
00:09:30,919 --> 00:09:33,159
If the Crown Prince, I mean...

199
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,960
If I travel hundreds of miles

200
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,080
to propose to Nuowu,

201
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,360
the news spreads,

202
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:39,320
your reputation is restored,

203
00:09:39,559 --> 00:09:40,440
and Nuowu could

204
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:43,159
stand tall among all tribes!

205
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,080
Young Master.

206
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,639
I think it

207
00:09:45,799 --> 00:09:46,799
makes sense.

208
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,399
I'd like to see

209
00:09:48,559 --> 00:09:49,919
what other tricks he has.

210
00:09:50,919 --> 00:09:51,559
Bring him up.

211
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:12,759
What's wrong?

212
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:15,000
This is my first time

213
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:16,759
leaving Dali.

214
00:10:18,639 --> 00:10:19,720
From now on,

215
00:10:20,879 --> 00:10:22,080
the sky shall be my blanket

216
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:23,720
and the earth my bed.

217
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:27,000
All hardships I endure...

218
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:34,679
You touched me?

219
00:10:36,799 --> 00:10:37,559
No, no.

220
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,600
I saw spiderwebs on you.

221
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,000
Let me clean them.

222
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,159
Let me help you.

223
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:47,120
Single-sack?

224
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,840
Someone recommended me

225
00:10:50,559 --> 00:10:51,399
to the Beggar Sect.

226
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:52,960
I see.

227
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:55,720
A single-sack?

228
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,120
We're peers.

229
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,320
I'm truly impressed.

230
00:11:05,799 --> 00:11:06,879
You're a five-sack member?

231
00:11:08,519 --> 00:11:09,399
My apologies.

232
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:11,799
What's your name?

233
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:12,840
They call me...

234
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,120
Just call me Xing.

235
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:16,720
Xing?

236
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:20,360
May I have your name?

237
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,080
The world knows me

238
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,399
as Dongfang Yushu.

239
00:11:26,679 --> 00:11:29,080
"Yushu" as in "dashingly handsome".

240
00:11:31,559 --> 00:11:32,320
Call me Dazhuang.

241
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:35,080
So Yushu...

242
00:11:36,039 --> 00:11:36,559
Well,

243
00:11:36,679 --> 00:11:37,480
just use Dazhuang.

244
00:11:37,799 --> 00:11:38,480
So I

245
00:11:38,519 --> 00:11:39,440
can call you Dazhuang?

246
00:11:39,679 --> 00:11:40,440
Sure.

247
00:11:52,879 --> 00:11:53,519
Why spit on me?

248
00:11:53,519 --> 00:11:54,200
Showing respect!

249
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,600
The Legend of Hero Xiao Feng

250
00:11:56,639 --> 00:11:57,320
says all

251
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:58,360
junior disciples

252
00:11:58,679 --> 00:12:01,000
must spit on senior disciples

253
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,039
to show respect.

254
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:02,919
So I...

255
00:12:02,919 --> 00:12:03,600
That's outdated.

256
00:12:03,759 --> 00:12:04,879
It's a bad custom.

257
00:12:04,919 --> 00:12:05,840
We don't do that.

258
00:12:05,879 --> 00:12:06,559
Stop spitting.

259
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:07,639
It's embarrassing.

260
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,519
And it's dirty.

261
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:11,399
Use wine to disinfect.

262
00:12:13,039 --> 00:12:13,360
Alright.

263
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:15,559
Listen.

264
00:12:15,759 --> 00:12:16,559
I made

265
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:17,639
this herb wine myself.

266
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:18,679
It can disinfect,

267
00:12:18,919 --> 00:12:19,879
also soothe injuries

268
00:12:20,039 --> 00:12:21,679
after getting beaten.

269
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:23,000
What?

270
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,559
Aren't you a five-sack?

271
00:12:27,159 --> 00:12:27,960
Well,

272
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,279
I mean,

273
00:12:29,639 --> 00:12:30,919
if I hit someone too hard,

274
00:12:31,279 --> 00:12:32,039
they could

275
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:32,879
use this.

276
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:35,639
Even the Shaolin Abbot praised it.

277
00:12:36,679 --> 00:12:37,679
How is the abbot now?

278
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:43,679
Well,

279
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,639
after hearing about you,

280
00:12:45,799 --> 00:12:47,639
he said you're outstanding,

281
00:12:48,519 --> 00:12:49,840
and wanted to treat you

282
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,039
to hotpot one day.

283
00:12:52,519 --> 00:12:54,840
The Abbot eats hotpot?

284
00:12:56,759 --> 00:12:57,679
That's not the point.

285
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:02,000
How can he tell you this

286
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,320
from Shaolin Temple?

287
00:13:05,679 --> 00:13:06,440
Via voice.

288
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,080
Voice transmission.

289
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:09,840
Listen.

290
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,679
Abbot!

291
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:22,919
I have told

292
00:13:22,919 --> 00:13:26,720
what you told me to Xing.

293
00:13:35,879 --> 00:13:36,200
Okay.

294
00:13:37,519 --> 00:13:38,399
He knows it.

295
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:42,080
You heard him?

296
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:42,759
Can't you?

297
00:13:45,879 --> 00:13:46,279
Amazing.

298
00:13:46,279 --> 00:13:47,120
Truly impressive.

299
00:13:47,679 --> 00:13:48,399
You know this,

300
00:13:48,519 --> 00:13:51,240
and master
the 18 Dragon-Subduing Palms.

301
00:13:51,639 --> 00:13:52,519
